# Copy to .env.local (local dev). Do not commit .env.local.
#
# Contact form (Next.js /contact):
# The page calls GET /api/contact — if CONTACT_SMTP_USER + CONTACT_SMTP_PASS are set,
# submissions use Nodemailer (POST /api/contact). Otherwise the browser uses FormSubmit.
# No NEXT_PUBLIC flag required for SMTP once server env is set + redeployed.
#
# Optional FormSubmit inbox when SMTP is off (default info.zssoft@gmail.com):
#   CONTACT_FORMSUBMIT_EMAIL — used by POST /api/contact (server)
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSUBMIT_EMAIL — used by the browser FormSubmit path (same default if unset)
# Optional: NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_FORCE_FORMSUBMIT=true — always use browser FormSubmit even if SMTP exists
#
# Vercel / Netlify / etc.: add the same keys in the dashboard
# (e.g. Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables) for Production, then Redeploy.
#
# Who receives SMTP enquiries: optional CONTACT_RECIPIENT_EMAIL (comma-separated).
# If omitted, mail goes to CONTACT_SMTP_USER (same account as the sender).
#
# SMTP: Google account with 2-Step Verification + App Password:
#   https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

CONTACT_SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
CONTACT_SMTP_PORT=465
CONTACT_SMTP_USER=yunus@zssofttech.com
CONTACT_SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-app-password

# Optional — defaults to "ZS Soft Tech Website <CONTACT_SMTP_USER>"
# CONTACT_FROM=ZS Soft Tech <yunus@zssofttech.com>

# If 465 is blocked, try:
# CONTACT_SMTP_PORT=587
# CONTACT_SMTP_SECURE=false
#
# --- Local troubleshooting (no mail) ---
# 1) Put vars in `.env.local` at the project root (same folder as package.json), then restart `npm run dev`.
# 2) Gmail: use an App Password (2-Step Verification on). Paste with or without spaces — spaces are stripped.
# 3) If the form succeeds but nothing arrives: check Spam; for SMTP, the `to:` address is CONTACT_RECIPIENT_EMAIL
#    or the same as CONTACT_SMTP_USER.
# 4) Without CONTACT_SMTP_USER + CONTACT_SMTP_PASS, the site uses FormSubmit to NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSUBMIT_EMAIL
#    (default info.zssoft@gmail.com) — that inbox must be activated once at https://formsubmit.co
# 5) On submit failure in dev, the red error line includes the server message (e.g. Invalid login).
#
# --- Gmail: "535-5.7.8 Username and Password not accepted" (BadCredentials) ---
# - CONTACT_SMTP_USER must be the full Gmail address for the account you sign in with (e.g. info.zssoft@gmail.com).
# - CONTACT_SMTP_PASS must be a 16-character App Password for THAT same account — not your normal Gmail password.
#   Create one with 2-Step Verification on: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# - Generate the App Password while logged into the inbox you use in CONTACT_SMTP_USER (not a different Google account).
# - Do not wrap the password in quotes in .env unless the whole value is quoted; stray quotes break login.
# - If it still fails: revoke old app passwords, create a new "Mail" app password, paste it into .env.local, restart `npm run dev`.
